# Design Polish — Incremental Only

Use the **Hallmark** skill (`hallmark`) for visual/UX quality when building or refining CMS UI. Prefer small, targeted improvements over greenfield redesigns.

## Default mode for this repo

- **Polish in place** — tighten hierarchy, spacing, contrast, badge/status color, empty states, motion restraint.
- **Keep the shell** — glass surfaces, sidebar, shadcn/ui, Tailwind tokens, and existing list/form layouts stay.
- **Do not** swap the whole CMS look (new theme catalog, new hero rhythm, global font/color overhaul) unless the user explicitly asks for a redesign or `hallmark redesign`.

## When Hallmark is appropriate

- New screens that still must match the current CMS language
- `hallmark audit <target>` — ranked punch list only, no edits
- Scoped polish (badges, tables, panels, forms) called out by the user
- Landing/marketing pages only if the user asks for that surface

## Hard stops

- Do not delete route trees or rewrite `components/ui/`
- Do not replace established patterns (CmsList*, GlassSurface, action toasts) with a new design system
- If a “redesign” would touch many unrelated files, stop and confirm scope first

## Stack constraints (still apply)

Next.js App Router · shadcn/ui · Tailwind v4 · English UI copy · Tailwind-first styling
